## Part 1: Write and Test Your Functions

### Function 1: `divide_and_round()`

**1. Write code to manipulate the vector of numbers `nums`. Your code should divide each element in the vector by the smallest element and then round the results to the nearest whole number.** 
*This code should not be a function!*


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
# Add your code below.
nums <- 3:12
```
:::


**2. Turn your code from Q1 into a function called `divide_and_round()`.** 
*Fill in the skeleton below.*


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
# Complete the function.
divide_and_round <- function(vec){

}
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
divide_and_round <- function(vec){
  min_elm <- min(vec, na.rm = TRUE)
  divided <- vec/min_elm
  rounded <- round(divided)
  return(rounded)
}
```
:::


**3. Test your function by running the code below.** Make sure the output is as expected. You may need to go back to Q2 and make changes to your function!


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
